<b>Syntax:</b>
<kbd>
<b>{scope [extend]} ... {/scope}</b>
</kbd>
<p>
<b>Attributes</b>
<p>
<dl compact>
<dt><kbd>extend</kbd>
<dd>Copy all variables from the outer scope.
</dl>
<p>
<b>Purpose</b>
<p>
Creates a new variable scope, so that any variable changes
(see <kbd><b>{set}</b></kbd>) in the scope won't affect later code.<br>
Also usefull for controling which (if any) variables that are visible
to included CGI-scripts:<br>
<kbd><b>{scope}</b>
{set variable=id value=test}{insert file=foo.cgi}
<b>{/scope}</b></kbd>
